splash.splashContent:
Welcome to SeniorServe!

Your one-stopweb application to provide seniors and people who care about them quick access to information related to health and care facilities across the province of Nova-Scotia.

Access the information icon in the top right for more information about this application and the tools it provides.

about.aboutContent:
This Web application was created using ESRI's WebApp Builder as a part of the ESRI Canada Centre of Excellence AppChallenge 2020.

It was created by the team "Better Call COGS" which includes Amanda Ring, Rafael Del Bello, and Sukhjit Pelia.

How to use the widgets?

1. Find Facilities by Location


This widget helps you to find facilities like Long-Term Care Centres & Hospitals across Nova Scotia based on either Town or County that you choose. Simply select your preference for e.g. Town and Hants and the map will zoom to that location. The Results Summary widget (4) can be launched to see details about the the surrounding area.


2. Nearby Facilities


This widget allows you to either search an address, locate your position on the map, or use a interactively point to a location in the map and see a summarized list of either Senior Safety Programs, Public Housing Units or Bingo Facilities based on the buffer zone. Additionally, you can click on the results in the same panel to view the approximate distance in Kilometres from your chosen location and a summarized information about the place.


3. Search by Facilities Amenities


This widget allows you to discover locations based on several parameters. For example, choose a surgical procedure you are looking for e.g. Knee Replacement – Partial and combine it with other filter e.g. Hospitals being a Community Hospital and the map shows the locations based on your filter. Make sure you enable the filters you want to apply. See the detailed with the help of Results Summary widget (4)


4. Results Summary


This widget summarizes all the features present within the current map extent. The results changes dynamically based on the zoom level.


5. Surgical Wait Times


This widget gives you an overview of the Surgical wait times across the province of Nova Scotia. You can filter the results across the whole province, or you can search for a medical procedure by choosing a location on the map and applying a search radius around that location. This widget switches to the results tab.



The information provided in this application is derived from the Nova Scotia Open Data Catalogue available at this location: https://data.novascotia.ca

The data sets include:
  • Surgical Wait Times
  • Location of Hospitals
  • Long Term and Residential Care Facilities
  • Long Term and Residential Care Facilities Directory (Link)
  • Public Housing Units
  • Nova Scotia Communities Engaged in Age-Friendly Community Planning
  • Bingo Licenses
  • Metropolitan Regional Housing Authority
  • Nova Scotia Counties with Senior Safety Programs.

Disclaimer:The information provided by this application"SeniorServe"is created for general and educational purposes only and is not a substitute for professional advice.


For official information about the process and arrangement for placement, please contact the Official Nova Scotia Health Department at the following toll-free number 1-800-225-7225.
